  <TITLE>Cache directories between builds</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Travis supports caching of directories. In my case with maven and java I'm downloading a lot of libraries from maven central. These are stored in ~/.m2/repository and it would be nice to persist this between runs using the same image. I was looking into docker volumes, either a mounted host directory or a shared volume between containers, but I'm not sure how to use it in relation to Drone. Would be nice if each container created by Drone is allowed to write in the shared volume to keep one up-to-date mvn repository. Any ideas on this?</DESCRIPTION>
